{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὀρφᾰνός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> also ός, όν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 149 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>orphan, without parents, fatherless,</b> αἱ δ᾽ ἐλίποντο ὀρφαναί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.68; ὀ. τέκνα 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 330; παῖδά τ᾽ ὀ. λιπεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 653 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: as <i>substantive</i>, <b>orphan,</b> ἐπίκληροι καὶ ὀ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 26.12; ὀρφανοῖς καὶ ὀρφαναῖς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 926c; ὀρφανῶν κάκωσις 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ath.” 56.6, compare “IG” 12.6.124: also in _neuter_, εἰς ὀρφανὰ καὶ ἔρημα ὑβρίζειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 927c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of animals, ὄρνις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1361 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀ. οἶκος, δόμος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 943, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 657 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>neglected,</b> ἡ δέλτος ὀρφανὴ κεῖται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 3.15 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; ὀρφανὰ κεῖται σκῦλα epigram cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 1.13.3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>bereaved</b> or <b>bereft of,</b> <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> of children, ὀ. πατρός <b>reft</b> of father, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 914, 1010; τοῦ πατρὸς ὀ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 57.70; γονέων 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.293d, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of parents, πότμον ὀρφανὸν γενεᾶς childless, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 9.61 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀ. παιδός, τέκνων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 149 (_anapaest meter_), “fragment” 332.6; νεοσσῶν ὀρφανὸν λέχος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 425. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> generally, ὀ. ἑτάρων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 7(6).10, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 730d; νύμφας ἔθηκεν ὀρφανὰς ξυναόρων 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1136; ἐπιστήμης 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus2.147a; κρατός Sositheus Tragicus 2.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀρφανοὶ ὕβριος <b>free from</b> insolence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).8(26); ψόφον.. Κασταλίας ὀρφανὸν ἀνδρῶν χορεύσιος [prev. author] “Pae.” 6.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀ. μαχᾶν, ={ἀπόμαχος}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Timotheus Lyricus “Persae” 154 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀρφανὴ βίου, i.e. <b>poor,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 3.39; ὀ. ἀγκίστρου κάλαμος “Anthologia Graeca” 12.42 (3rd c.BC: Dioscorides Epigrammaticus): Comedy texts _metaphorically_, ὀ. ταρίχιον\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] salt-fish <b>without sauce,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 22 (uncertain reading). (A shorter form ὀρφο- appears in ὀρφο-βότης (which see), ὀρφόω,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] cf. Latin <i>orbus,</i> Gothic <i>arbi</i> 'inheritance'.)","strongNumber":"G3737","accentedUnicode":"ὀρφανός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0642","matchingForm":"ἀπορφανίζω","stepTransliteration":"aporfanizō","gloss":"to orphan","_zh_tw_Gloss":"離別","_es_Gloss":"dejar huérfano","_zh_Gloss":"离别"}],"shortDef":"(n.) an orphan","mediumDef":"(n.) an orphan <br /><b>bereaved</b>, of parents, <b>orphan,</b> <ref='Jas.1.27'>Jas. 1:27;</ref> <b>bereaved, desolate,</b> <r